Code : Interesting Alphabets
Send Feedback
Print the following pattern for the given number of rows.
Pattern for N = 5
E
DE
CDE
BCDE
ABCDE
Input format :
N (Total no. of rows)
Output format :
Pattern in N lines
Constraints
0 <= N <= 26
Sample Input 1:
8
Sample Output 1:
H
GH
FGH
EFGH
DEFGH
CDEFGH
BCDEFGH
ABCDEFGH
Sample Input 2:
7
Sample Output 2:
G
FG
EFG
DEFG
CDEFG
BCDEFG
ABCDEFG


                                                       OUTPUT:-
                                                       
                                                       
import java.util.*;
public class Solution {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		//Your code goes here
        Scanner scn=new Scanner(System.in);
        int n =scn.nextInt();
        
            for(int i=1;i<=n;i++){
                int ch=n+64-i+1;
                for(int j=1;j<=i;j++){
                    System.out.print((char)ch);
                    ch++;
                }
                System.out.println();
            
        }
	}
}
